        <div id="problem">
            <h2>The Problem</h2>
            <h4>DVSTY’s current website does not adequately communicate the brand’s messaging to its target audience as being Boston’s most unique consignment shop for luxury and vintage clothes, music, art.The current website does not reinforce DVSTY’s brand identity in a way that resonates with the target audience. 
            </h4>
        </div>
        <div id="objective">
            <h2>Project Objective</h2>
            <h4>Redesign DVSTY’s website to give information to re-introduce the customer to the brand’s identity/aesthetic, showcase the product categories, provide contact information/hours of operation, and communicate brand messaging.
            </h4>
        </div>
        <div id="target">
            <h2>Target Audience</h2>
            <h4>DVSTY caters to a large audience, primarily between the ages of 16-65. More specifically, as a consignment store, DVSTY's target audience are those with an affinity for vintage and luxury items and those that want to make some money by allowing DVSTY to re-sell their vintage and luxury pieces. The other consignment stores in the Boston area tend to be particulary catered to women, so the intent is to make it clear that there is something for all genders for sale at DVSTY.</h4>
        </div>
    </div>
  

